casebody.data:
McSorley, Appellant, v. Deeves, Respondent. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. December 19, 1889.) Appeal from eleventh district court.

Argued before Van Hoesen, P. J., and Bookstaver, J.

Thornton, Earle & Kiendl, for appellant. Blandy & Hatch, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be reversed, new trial ordered, costs to abide the event.
